NameChapDNSUpdateV2
Overview
NameChapDNSUpdateV2 is a .NET console application designed to update DNS records on NameCheap automatically. The application runs checks at intervals to update the DNS records if the public IP changes.

Features
Automatic DNS updates
Environment variable-based configuration
JSON serialization and deserialization for API responses
Prerequisites
.NET SDK
NameCheap account with domain and Dynamic DNS enabled
Installation
Clone the repository:
bash
Copy code
git clone https://github.com/lyte99/NameChapDNSUpdateV2.git
Navigate to the project directory:
bash
Copy code
cd NameChapDNSUpdateV2
Configuration
Set the following environment variables:

domain: Your domain name (e.g., example.com)
hosts: List of hosts separated by semicolons (e.g., @;www)
dynamicDNSPassword: Your Dynamic DNS password from NameCheap
Usage
Run the application:

arduino
Copy code
dotnet run
Testing
The project includes unit tests to validate its functionality. To run the tests, navigate to the test project directory and execute:

bash
Copy code
dotnet test
